we were dealing with, the fact that all students

05:20.740 --> 05:35.214
couldn't get in for interviews, and these kinds of 
things. And it sometimes gave me concern that we

05:35.294 --> 05:49.228
just didn't have as much data as we'd like to have, 
and we're doing it on the, that we obviously, we may

05:35.294 --> 05:49.228
be overlooking some factors in a student's life 
that might be very beneficial in making the

05:49.580 --> 05:56.068
selection. Which is more important, the score in 
the verbal or the mathematical? Statistically,

06:02.976 --> 06:06.280
the verbal score is more important. And the 
selection

